OL,3,CFathers protest about 'inadequate'
OL,4,Cpaternity leave
OL,6,F"Fathers are being forced back to work
OL,7,Fbefore they're ready and when they're
OL,8,Fneeded most. These men are caught
OL,9,Fbetween the stress of keeping their
OL,10,Ffamilies afloat financially, trying to
OL,11,Fbe there for their partners and new
OL,12,Fbabies, and the demand to perform at
OL,13,Fwork as if nothing has changed.
OL,15,F"They have little choice but to suffer
OL,16,Fin silence and try to soldier on, even
OL,17,Fif it breaks them."
OL,19,FThe organisation also highlighted that
OL,20,Fpoor paternity leave also impacts
OL,21,Fmothers.
